title: Peripsocus milleri
text:
Peripsocus milleri is a species of <a href="Psocoptera">Psocoptera</a> from the <a href="Peripsocidae">Peripsocidae</a> family that can be found in <a href="Great%20Britain">Great Britain</a> and <a href="Ireland">Ireland</a>. They can also be found on <a href="Azores">Azores</a> and <a href="Canary%20Islands">Canary Islands</a>, <a href="Belgium">Belgium</a>, <a href="Croatia">Croatia</a>, <a href="France">France</a>, <a href="Italy">Italy</a>, and <a href="Spain">Spain</a>. The species are <a href="brown">brown</a> coloured.
Habitat.
The species feed om <a href="oak">oak</a>s.
